The paper deals with lower bounds for the running time of algorithms for various optimization problems, which suggests that it could belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The use of Label Cover and projection constraints also suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.CG). The mention of approximation algorithms and ratios suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
